<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Outline: inherit with three values</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/ui.html#propdef-outline" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Outline with value inherit uses its parent's outline values (3 values)." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                outline: 15px red solid;
                outline: inherit;
            }
            #wrapper
            {
                outline: green 15px dotted;
                height: 50px;
                padding: 50px 50px 50px 50px;
                border: solid 2px blue;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a green outline closely surrounding the following text that is the same as the outline surrounding the blue box and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="wrapper">
            <div id="div1">Filler text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>